    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-05-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-05-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="369"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d369">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/4167</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Secretary of the Navy</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_DJ1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Daniels</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-05-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 2, 1917</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your communication of April 27, 1917, relative to the offer made by the <hi
                        rend="italic">de facto</hi> Government of Costa Rica through its
                    representative in Washington of the harbors and ports of that Republic for the
                    use of the United States in the prosecution of war against Germany.</p>
                <p>In reply to your inquiry in this connection I have the honor to inform you that
                    due to the fact that no recognition has been accorded the
                        <persName>Tinoco</persName> government in Costa Rica by the Government of
                    the United States, no action has been taken upon the offer to which reference is
                    made.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Frank L. Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Counselor</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
